use or neglect with timely expert medical evaluations and treatment  and serves the community as a resource for prevention  research and education  Located at      N  Rockton Ave  in Rockford  this program receives referrals from the Department of Family and Community Services  law enforcement and physicians in northwest Illinois We accept most insurance and have strong affiliations with our local health care partners  SwedishAmerican  A Division of UW Health  Mercyhealth and OSF Saint Anthony Medical Center  In addition to our College of Medicine Rockford facilities  many hospitals  clinics  treatment centers  hospices and other health care facilities in the Rockford area serve as teaching sites  Many doctors in the area are on our faculty and train medical students and residents in their practices throughout Rockford and around the state Patient Forms   ResourcesPatient Release of Information Form  print and mail or fax to the clinic print and mail or fax to the clinic Patient Care Providing the best possible care to our patients  while teaching the next generation of doctors  is at the heart of all the patient care facilities operated by the University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford  These include  UI Health L P  Johnson Family Health Center UI Health L P  Johnson Family Health Center The University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford operates the L P  Johnson Family Health Center  a unique family practice that is home to our Family Medicine Residency Program  Focused on preventive medicine and health care for the whole family  this health center is located at      State Street in Rockford UI Health Thyroid Disease in Pregnancy Clinic UI Health Thyroid Disease in Pregnancy Clinic The UI Health Thyroid Disease in Pregnancy Clinic at the      Parkview Ave  site in Rockford is a specialty clinic for pregnant women with thyroid conditions Medical Evaluation Response Initiative Team  MERIT Medical Evaluation Response Initiative Team  MERIT The Medical E